The book is kept at the least distance of distance vision $D=25 \mathrm{~cm}$, i.e., $u=-25 \mathrm{~cm}$ and corrective lenses used form the clear images at 90 cm , which is the near point of person, i.e., $v=-90 \mathrm{~cm}$. Therefore, according to the lens formula, we have
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{1}{v}-\frac{1}{u}=\frac{1}{f} \\
\Rightarrow & \frac{1}{-90}-\frac{1}{-25}=\frac{1}{f} \Rightarrow \frac{1}{f}=\frac{-5+18}{450} \Rightarrow f=34.6 \mathrm{~cm}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& L=v_{o}+u_{e}=\frac{u_{o} f_{o}}{\left(u_{o}-f_{o}\right)}+\frac{f_{e} D}{f_{e}+D} \\
& \Rightarrow L=\frac{2 \times 1.5}{(2-1.5)}+\frac{6.25 \times 25}{(6.25+25)}=11 \mathrm{~cm}
\end{aligned}
$$

As here $u=-0.25 \mathrm{~m}$ and $\mathrm{f}=1 / \mathrm{P}=(1 / 3) \mathrm{m}$, from lens formula $P=\frac{1}{f}=\frac{1}{v}-\frac{1}{u}$, we have $3=\frac{1}{v}-\frac{1}{-0.25}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \text { or } \frac{1}{v}=3-4=-1 \mathrm{~m} \\
& \text { i.e. } v=-1 \mathrm{~m}
\end{aligned}
$$
i.e., the lens shifts the object from 25 cm to 1 m for clear vision, i.e., his near point is 1 m . So in absence of glasses, he must hold the newspaper at a distance of 1 m away from his eyes for clear vision.

The person is suffering from myopia. This defect is corrected by using a concave lens of suitable focal length i.e., power.
$$
\begin{aligned}
\text { Power } & =\frac{-1}{\text { far point (metre) }}=\frac{-1}{1.2}=\frac{-10}{12} \\
& =\frac{-5}{6}=-0.83 \text { dioptre }
\end{aligned}
$$

(i) Distant vision
(ii) For near vision
$$
\begin{array}{ll}
P=-\frac{1}{f(\text { metre })} & f=\frac{1}{P}=\frac{1}{1.5} \\
f=-\frac{1}{P}=\frac{1}{5.5}=\frac{-10}{55} & f=\frac{10}{15} \times 100 \mathrm{~cm} \\
f=-\frac{2}{11} \mathrm{~m}=\frac{-2}{11} \times 100 \mathrm{~cm} & f=\frac{200}{3} \mathrm{~cm} \\
f=-\frac{200}{11} \mathrm{~cm}=-18.2 \mathrm{~cm} & f=+66.67 \mathrm{~cm}
\end{array}
$$

The lens used for correcting the disease is concave lens
$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathrm{P} & =-\frac{1}{\text { far point (metre) }}=-\frac{1}{80 \mathrm{~cm}}=\frac{-100}{80} \\
& =-1.25 \mathrm{D}
